|Boeing 737-800]]\n|7<ref>https://www.businesstraveller.com/business-travel/2020/01/15/vistara-phases-out-boeing-737-aircraft/</ref>\n| \u2014<ref name=\"India's Vistara launches B737-800 ops\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.businesstoday.in/sectors/aviation/vistara-starts-phasing-out-9-boeing-737-planes/story/393665.html|title=Vistara to start phasing out it's 9 737-800|last=|first=|date=|website=ch-aviation|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-06-08}}</ref>\n|12\n|&mdash; \n|156 \n|168\n|Former [[Jet Airways]] aircraft<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://in.reuters.com/article/india-vistara-aircraft-idINKCN1SU15R|title=Vistara leases six planes from BOC Aviation for local expansion|date=24 May 2019|via=in.reuters.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Boeing 787|Boeing 787-9]]\n|1\n|5<ref name=\"NewJets\">{{cite news|url=https://in.reuters.com/article/vistara-orders-boeing-airbus/vistara-orders-boeing-airbus-jets-worth-31-billion-in-growth-plan-idINKBN1K10JL|title=Vistara orders Boeing, Airbus jets worth $3.1 billion in growth plan|accessdate=2018-07-12|date=2018-07-11|publisher=in.reuters.com|author=Aditi Shah, Jamie Freed}}</ref> \n|30\n|21\n|248\n|299\n|<ref> https://www.airvistara.com/trip/inflight-magazine/monthly/now </ref>\n|-\n! Total\n! 40\n! 52\n!colspan=\"6\" |\n|}\n</center>\n\nVistara took delivery of its first aircraft at New Delhi on 25 September 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/vistara-takes-delivery-of-first-airbus-a-320-aircraft-in-delhi-114092500958_1.html|title=Vistara takes delivery of first Airbus A320 aircraft in Delhi|newspaper=[[Business Standard]]|date=25 September 2014|access-date=25 September 2014|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141213022342/http://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/vistara-takes-delivery-of-first-airbus-a-320-aircraft-in-delhi-114092500958_1.html|archivedate=13 December 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The airline took delivery of the last of its thirteen original Airbus A320 aircraft in October 2016<ref name=induction>{{cite news |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/business/aviation/vistara-airlines-completes-induction-of-airbus-a320-planes-3074848/ |title=Vistara airlines completes induction of Airbus A320 planes |agency=[[Press Trust of India]] |publisher=The Express Group |website=[[The Indian Express]] |date=10 October 2016 |access-date=10 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161010204217/http://indianexpress.com/article/business/aviation/vistara-airlines-completes-induction-of-airbus-a320-planes-3074848/ |archivedate=10 October 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> and plans to receive its seven Airbus A320neo aircraft by mid-2018.<ref name=induction/> In March 2015, Phee Teik Yeoh announced that the airline was planning to procure an unspecified number of both narrow-body and wide-body aircraft to enhance the domestic network and launch international flights within two years.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/transportation/airlines-/-aviation/vistara-plans-to-add-international-routes-expand-fleet/articleshow/46756305.cms|title=Vistara plans to add international routes, expand fleet|newspaper=[[The Economic Times]]|date=31 March 2015|access-date=31 March 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150403052742/http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/transportation/airlines-/-aviation/vistara-plans-to-add-international-routes-expand-fleet/articleshow/46756305.cms|archivedate=3 April 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.financialexpress.com/article/companies/20-aircraft-target-by-2018-is-just-the-tip-of-the-iceberg-phee-teik-yeoh-vistara-ceo/75021/|title=20-aircraft target by 2018 is just the tip of the iceberg: Phee Teik Yeoh, Vistara CEO|newspaper=[[The Financial Express (India)|Financial Express]]|date=23 May 2015|access-date=24 August 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924013000/http://www.financialexpress.com/article/companies/20-aircraft-target-by-2018-is-just-the-tip-of-the-iceberg-phee-teik-yeoh-vistara-ceo/75021/|archivedate=24 September 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The airline recently inducted a number of former Jet Airways Boeing [[737-800|737-800NG]] to its fleet.<ref name=\"auto1\"/>Vistara is returning two of these nine leased Boeing 737 planes from January and the remaining seven will exit the fleet between 2022-23 as they are on long term.<ref>{{cite news |title=Vistara starts phasing out 9 Boeing 737 planes- Business News |url=https://www.businesstoday.in/sectors/aviation/vistara-starts-phasing-out-9-boeing-737-planes/story/393665.html |accessdate=5 March 2020 |work=www.businesstoday.in}}</ref>\n\n==Services==\n===Cabin===\n====Business class====\nVistara offers 8 business class seats, two rows in 2-2 configuration, in its 158-seater Airbus A320-200 fleet. The business class seats are {{convert|20.12|in}} wide with {{convert|42|in}} [[seat pitch]].<ref name=\"Cabin re-config\">{{cite news|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/transportation/airlines-/-aviation/vistara-reduces-seats-in-premium-class-cabins/articleshow/51189795.cms|title=Vistara reduces seats in premium class cabins|newspaper=[[The Economic Times]]|date=29 February 2016|accessdate=17 August 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161024160435/http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/transportation/airlines-/-aviation/vistara-reduces-seats-in-premium-class-cabins/articleshow/51189795.cms|archivedate=24 October 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Flight Review\">{{cite news|url=http://www.bangaloreaviation.com/2015/03/inflight-review-vistara-business-class-airbus-a320-hyderabad-new-delhi.html|title=Inflight review: Vistara Business Class: Airbus A320: Hyderabad \u2013 New Delhi|work=Bangalore Aviation|date=25 March 2015|access-date=25 March 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150327184400/http://www.bangaloreaviation.com/2015/03/inflight-review-vistara-business-class-airbus-a320-hyderabad-new-delhi.html|archivedate=27 March 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n====Premium Economy====\nVistara was the first airline in India to introduce Premium Economy class in the domestic market.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/vistara-takes-the-premium-economy-way-114122300979_1.html|title=Vistara takes the premium economy way|newspaper=[[Business Standard]]|date=23 December 2014|access-date=2 March 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150114164451/http://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/vistara-takes-the-premium-economy-way-114122300979_1.html|archivedate=14 January 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref> At present it offers 24 premium economy seats, four rows in 3-3 configuration, out of total 158 seats in the single aisle Airbus A320-200 aircraft in its fleet. Each being {{convert|18|in}} wide and having a pitch of {{convert|33-36|in}}.<ref name=\"Cabin re-config\"/>\n\n===In-flight entertainment===\nVistara World is the airline's wireless Wi-Fi inflight entertainment system that travellers can access on their personal handheld devices. Vistara selected a wireless IFE solution from Bluebox Aviation Systems to enable this service.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://blueboxaviation.com/bbwow-vistara/|title=Bluebox Wow to Fly Indian Skies with Vistara {{!}} Bluebox|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-06-25}}</ref> It offers a multimedia library of over 70 hours\u2019 Bollywood and Hollywood content of various genres. It features movies of various categories such as Drama, Romance, Comedy, Thriller, Action, Adventure and Kids, as well as popular Indian and Western TV programmes and a selection of music including Indian, Pop, Jazz, Blues, Rock, Electronica and English Retro. Vistara World offers a live moving map display that allows one to track their aircraft as it flies.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/|title=Business News, Shares Market, Stock Markets News LIVE \u2013 IPO, Mutual Funds, Income Tax and Finance News|website=Mint|language=en|access-date=2019-06-25}}</ref>\n\n===Catering===\nThe in-flight food is catered by [[SATS Ltd|TajSATS Air Catering]], another joint venture between Tata and a Singaporean company, headed by Chef Arun Batra, formerly the executive chef of the [[Taj Hotels Resorts and Palaces|Taj Hotels]] group.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/industry-and-economy/logistics/food-in-high-places/article6827221.ece|title=Food in high places|newspaper=[[The Hindu]]|date=27 January 2015|access-date=2 March 2015}}</ref> Vistara offers four different meals for each cabin for different time of the day \u2013 breakfast, refreshment, lunch and dinner with options of one vegetarian and one non-vegetarian dish in economy class; two vegetarian dishes and one non-vegetarian dish in premium economy; and two vegetarian and two non-vegetarian dishes for business-class cabin. The menu is typically changed every seventh day and there are different menus for lunch and dinner.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://networkthoughts.in/vistaras-chefs-table-with-chef-arun-batra-giam-ming-toh-part-i/|title=Vistara\u2019s Chef\u2019s Table: With Chef Arun Batra & Giam Ming Toh|work=Network Thought|date=21 August 2015|access-date=17 September 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150826021043/http://networkthoughts.in/vistaras-chefs-table-with-chef-arun-batra-giam-ming-toh-part-i/|archivedate=26 August 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref> It also provides special meals upon request 24 hours before departure.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.airvistara.com/trip/vistara-experience#inflight-dining-experience|title=Vistara:Inflight Dining|publisher=Vistara|access-date=22 August 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150709090330/https://www.airvistara.com/trip/vistara-experience#inflight-dining-experience|archivedate=9 July 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/flying-and-feasting/article7569653.ece|title=Flying and feasting|newspaper=[[The Hindu]]|date=22 August 2015|access-date=3 September 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151110194945/http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/flying-and-feasting/article7569653.ece|archivedate=10 November 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Lounge===\nOn 29 March 2016, Vistara inaugurated premium lounge service for its Business-class passengers and ''Club Vistara'' Platinum & Gold members at the departure level of Terminal 3 of Indira Gandhi International Airport at Delhi. The lounge was spread across 250 square metres on the air-side and could seat 75 people at a time.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/vistara-unveils-signature-lounge-at-igi-airport-116032901204_1.html |title=Vistara unveils signature lounge at IGI airport |work=[[Business Standard]] |date=29 March 2016 |accessdate=29 March 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160402053446/http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/vistara-unveils-signature-lounge-at-igi-airport-116032901204_1.html |archivedate=2 April 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> However, on April 8th, Vistara sent an email to all its member's confirming that they are closing down the lounge due to the expiry of their lease at the airport.\n\n==Frequent-flyer program==\nVistara uses ''Club Vistara'' as its [[frequent-flyer program]];<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.airvistara.com/trip/club-vistara|title=Club Vistara|publisher=Vistara|access-date=6 March 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151110194944/https://www.airvistara.com/trip/club-vistara|archivedate=10 November 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref> it operates as a value based program and awards points on the basis of money spent on tickets rather than miles travelled by passengers.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.financialexpress.com/article/industry/companies/full-service-airlines-go-full-tilt-at-loyalty-programmes/50957/|title=Full-service airlines Vistara, Jet Airways, Air India go full tilt at loyalty programmes|newspaper=[[The Financial Express (India)|Financial Express]]|date=7 March 2015|access-date=7 March 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150309010016/http://www.financialexpress.com/article/industry/companies/full-service-airlines-go-full-tilt-at-loyalty-programmes/50957/|archivedate=9 March 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 29 January 2015, Vistara announced a partnership agreement with [[Singapore Airlines]] which would allow Club Vistara members to earn and redeem miles with the [[KrisFlyer]] program on [[Singapore Airlines]] and [[SilkAir]] flights.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/money/report-vistara-launches-loyalty-scheme-with-singapor-airline-s-krisflyer-programme-2056571|title=Vistara launches loyalty scheme with Singapore Airline's KrisFlyer programme|newspaper=[[Daily News and Analysis]]|date=29 January 2015|access-date=2 March 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402100233/http://www.dnaindia.com/money/report-vistara-launches-loyalty-scheme-with-singapor-airline-s-krisflyer-programme-2056571|archivedate=2 April 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of airlines of India]]\n* [[List of airports in India]]\n* [[Transport in India]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category-inline|Vistara}}\n* {{official website|http://www.airvistara.com}}\n\n{{airlines of India}}\n{{Tata Group}}\n\n[[Category:Airlines established in 2013]]\n[[Category:Airlines of India]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Gurgaon]]\n[[Category:Tata Group]]\n[[Category:Singapore Airlines]]\n[[Category:2013 establishments in India]]\n[[Category:Indian brands]]\n", "name_user": "Raulnayak", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eLounge:corrected grammar", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vistara"}
